subSubSection.paragraph:
Mozambique · one specimen and vial with six parapodia; 
lectotype
ZMB 4005 · 3 adult specimens, same data as for the lectotype; 
paralectotypes
ZMB 47 · one specimen; same data as for the lectotype; ZMB F2046 · seven adult specimens; same data as for the lectotype; ZMB 4005.

Holotype complete (Fig. 
1A-F
), ventrally dissected (Fig. 
1C
), with 198 chaetigers, L10 = 8.2 mm, W10 = 2.5 mm, TL = 93 mm. Anterior region with dorsum convex, flat ventre, body depressed from chaetiger 6 (Fig. 
1D
), widest at chaetiger 17, tapering after chaetiger 41.

