subSubSection.paragraph:
Prostomium bilobed, 1.3 mm long, 1.6 mm wide; lobes frontally rounded; median sulcus shallow and deep ventrally (Fig. 
1A, B
). Prostomial appendages in semicircle, median antenna isolated by a gap. Palps reaching second peristomial ring; lateral antennae reaching first chaetiger; median antenna reaching second chaetiger. Palpophores and ceratophores ring-shaped, short, slender; palpostyles and ceratostyles tapering, thick. Eyes absent.

Peristomium (1.7 mm long, 2.3 mm wide) larger than prostomium, first ring twice as long as second ring, separation between rings distinct on all sides (Fig. 
1A-C
). Ventral lip dissected, with several shallow wrinkles (Fig. 
1C
).

